<section class="section" id="faq"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="center"><span class="eyebrow">Questions, answered</span><h2>What to know before you download.</h2></div>
  <div class="faq" data-faq>
    <details open><summary>How large a file can it really open?</summary><p>Around 10 GB comfortably. Files too large to index eagerly fall back to on-demand (lazy) indexing, so documents near or beyond your available RAM still open.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Which formats are supported?</summary><p>JSON, JSON-Lines / NDJSON, XML, CSV and TSV. The parser is chosen from the file extension, and you can also paste from the clipboard or open from a URL.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Does my data leave my machine?</summary><p>No. Files are memory-mapped and processed locally. Nothing is uploaded &mdash; the only network call is the optional Open-URL fetch you trigger yourself.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What platforms does it run on?</summary><p>Windows, macOS (universal, Apple Silicon + Intel) and Linux.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What's the difference between Free and paid editions?</summary><p>Free opens JSON up to 100 MB (XML/CSV any size). Premium and the Narik Edition remove the size limit and add automatic update checks; Enterprise adds volume licensing and managed deployment.</p></details>
  </div>
</div></section>

